WHEN the gogo rushed to a bus stop on her pension day about two months ago, her family thought she would be back after a few hours.Her worried daughter, Balungile Zuke (59) told Daily Sun that her mum disappeared on 11 October.&ldquo;We are beginning to think of the worst about her disappearance,&rdquo; she told the People&rsquo;s Paper.&ldquo;We are very worried and sometimes think she might have been killed by cruel people. &ldquo;We often hear of such stories where people are found killed after they have gone missing for days or even months. &ldquo;Some of these things are happening in nearby villages.&rdquo; Balungile said they have consulted many sangomas and spiritual healers, but they were told that their mum was still alive.&ldquo;My mum has a scar near her left eye and is of average build,&rdquo; she said.&ldquo;On the day she disappeared she was wearing a white and navy traditional dress, a cream jersey and navy takkies. KZN police spokeswoman Captain Nqobile Gwala confirmed a missing person&rsquo;s case was opened at Sawoti cop shop.&ldquo;Anyone with information about gogo Gadekile&rsquo;s whereabouts should contact Detective-Constable Nonhle Myende on 039 971 9000 or call 08600 10111,&rdquo; Gwala told the People&rsquo;s Paper.